<h1 id="associate-a-fuel-index-with-a-carrier-as-an-accessorial-charge">Associate a fuel index with a carrier as an accessorial charge</h1>


<p>This guide shows how to create an accessorial assignment, carrier accessorial charge, accessorial master for fuel surcharge, and associate a carrier fuel index with a carrier. You need to have set up a carrier fuel index before you run this guide. You can use the &quot;Set up a carrier fuel index&quot; guide to do this. These setup tasks are typically done by a Logistics manager. The demo data used to create this procedure is USMF.</p>
<h2 id="create-an-accessorial-master">Create an accessorial master</h2>
<ol>
<li>Go to Transportation management &gt; Setup &gt; Rating &gt; Accessorial masters.</li>
<li>Click New.</li>
<li>In the Accessorial master field, type a value.</li>
<li>In the Name field, type a value.</li>
<li>Click Save.</li>
</ol>
<h2 id="create-a-carrier-accessorial-charge">Create a carrier accessorial charge</h2>
<ol>
<li>Go to Transportation management &gt; Setup &gt; Rating &gt; Carrier accessorial charges.</li>
<li>Click New.</li>
<li>In the Carrier accessorial ID field, type a value.</li>
<li>In the Shipping carrier field, click the drop-down button to open the lookup.</li>
<li>In the list, find and select the desired record.
<ul>
<li>In this example, choose Truck Carrier.</li>
</ul>
</li>
<li>In the list, click the link in the selected row.</li>
<li>In the Carrier service field, click the drop-down button to open the lookup.</li>
<li>In the list, click the link in the selected row.</li>
<li>In the Accessorial master field, click the drop-down button to open the lookup.</li>
<li>In the list, find and select the desired record.
<ul>
<li>In this example, choose the newly created Accessorial master.</li>
</ul>
</li>
<li>Click Save.</li>
</ol>
<h2 id="create-an-accessorial-assignment">Create an accessorial assignment</h2>
<ol>
<li>Click Accessorial assignments.</li>
<li>Click New.</li>
<li>In the Name field, type a value.</li>
<li>Toggle the expansion of the Criteria section.
<ul>
<li>In the criteria, you can choose to always apply the fuel surcharge or for this example choose that it only applies within a certain region.</li>
</ul>
</li>
<li>In the ZIP/postal code from field, type a value.</li>
<li>In the ZIP/postal code to field, type a value.</li>
<li>Toggle the expansion of the Calculation section.
<ul>
<li>In the calculation section you can specify how to calculate the fuel surcharge. This calculation depends on the Accessorial unit that you chose as the base for your calculation.</li>
</ul>
</li>
<li>In the Accessorial fee type field, select 'Fuel surcharge'.</li>
<li>In the Accessorial unit field, select 'Mileage'.</li>
<li>In the Region field, click the drop-down button to open the lookup.</li>
<li>In the list, click the link in the selected row.</li>
<li>Click Save.</li>
</ol>
<h2 id="update-the-carrier-rating-profile">Update the carrier rating profile</h2>
<ol>
<li>Go to Transportation management &gt; Setup &gt; Carriers &gt; Shipping carriers.</li>
<li>In the list, find and select the desired record.</li>
<li>Toggle the expansion of the Rating profiles section.</li>
<li>Click Edit.</li>
<li>In the Carrier fuel index field, click the drop-down button to open the lookup.</li>
<li>In the list, click the link in the selected row.</li>
<li>Click Save.</li>
</ol>
